Google is a multinational technology company known for its internet-related products and services. It was founded in 1998 by Larry Page and Sergey Brin while they were Ph.D. students at Stanford University. Google's primary service is its search engine, which allows users to search for information on the internet. It also offers a wide range of other services, such as email (Gmail), cloud storage (Google Drive), online productivity suite (Google Docs, Sheets, Slides), web browsing (Google Chrome), and mobile operating system (Android), among others. Google is one of the most well-known and widely used technology companies in the world.
